le of sparge water to measure PH','',0,22,0,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]',0),(4347,'test@example.com','27AG28i29','Start Fly Sparging','',0,22,-1,'(SPARGE) Sparging will drain the sugar from the grain providing us with wort. The process of sparging should be carried out slowly. The temperature of the gain bed will be raised during this proess (note there is no instant change of temperature). The grain bed should stay below 76 deg C. We need to aim for a boil volume of ...boil_vol...L. General wisdom is to keep 1 inch of water above the grain bed- however there is a trade off (the more water above the grain bed the smaller/slower temperature rise of the grain bed, the less water above the grain bed the bigger/quicker temperature rise of the grain bed.','[\"dosparge.png\"]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]',1),(4346,'test@example.com','27AG28i29','First Wort Hopping','',0,21,-1,'Add the first wort hops to the boiler before starting to sparge','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'hopaddFirstWort_v3',1,0,'[\"first_wort_hop_qty\", \">\", \"0\"]',0),(4345,'test@example.com','27AG28i29','Collect sample of mash to measure PH','',0,20,2,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]',0),(4344,'test@example.com','27AG28i29','Allow up to 6 litres of wort to drain from the mash tun into the kettle, the wort should be carefully added back to the top of the lauter tun trying to ensure minimal disturbance.','',0,20,1,'','[]','','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]',0),(4342,'test@example.com','27AG28i29','Assemble Sparge Setup and begin Recirculation','',0,20,-1,'Once the sparge water is at the correct temperature ...sparge_temp...C AND the mash duration has completedthe sparge setup can be setup. During this step the cloudy wort with bits of grain will drained leading to a natural grain filter forming.','[\"spargesetup.png\"]','Set the thermometer to alarm if the temperature is higher than 71deg. If it is then lid should be lifted to reduce the heat.','',0,0,0,0,0,'',1,0,'[]',3),(4343,'test@example.com','27AG28i29','Ta